Barack Obama becomes fourth U.S. president to receive Nobel Peace Prize
U.S. President Barack Obama is coming to Oslo, Norway, for 26 hours to receive the Nobel Peace Prize as the fourth US president in history.
In addition, he receives the diploma, the medal and a cheque for 1.4 million. Dollars for his extraordinary aspirations to intensify world diplomacy and cooperation among peoples.
The White House chief arrives in the northbound metropolis tomorrow with his wife Michelle and will be busy all the time.
First, he pays a visit to the Nobel Institute, where he meets for the first time with the five committee members, who elected him in October from 172 people and 33 organizations.
The presidential couple then scheduled a meeting with the Norwegian king Harald V and Queen Sonja.
In the afternoon, the visit reaches its climax with the ceremony at which Obama takes over the prestigious prize.
He will receive this as the fourth US President, but only as the third, who accepts the prize directly in office.
The White House has already announced that Obama will talk about the Afghanistan war when taking over the prize.
The president does not want to dodge this issue because he knows that he is taking over the prize as a president who is currently waging war in two countries.
He stepped up the war effort a few days ago by sending more troops to Afghanistan, which none of his critics forget to highlight.
At the ceremony, Obama also received the Gol Medal, Diploma and Cheque for ten million Swedish crowns (approx. 24 million Czech crowns).
He intends to donate the money to charity, but he has not yet decided on a concrete charitable work.
The event programme will then include a banquet with the president and his wife, where, in addition to Norway's king and queen, the Prime Minister and another 250 invited guests will be present.
Obama was very cautious from the beginning on the price.
He said, for example, that he felt he didn’t quite deserve the prize.
Several times he also repeated that it is the price not only for him, but for all those who strive for the same values as him.
Immediately after the announcement, he listed that this is "call to action" for him.
