However, the following months showed that the Bush strategy based on recommendations of the military was the only possible and in this respect very successful that people no longer speak at all in the news about Iraq today.
Bush’s reputation was not improved by this, because objectively he left his successor a much more grateful starting situation than was to be expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes the miracle will repeat itself.
The military has again asked him to increase the troop quota, especially the commander-in-chief of Afghanistan operation General Stanley McCristal, who even despite the subordination habits harshly criticized the procrating shooters in the White House.
He called for 40,000 troops to be able to reverse the situation for the better.
The president hesitated for three months, but did not come up with a better idea and so he has at least cheated the general by 10,000 troops.
From Europe, he pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even if he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
Highly problematic about the entire Obama strategy is his intention to withdraw the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and to complete this process within three years. The whole Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the halved increase will bring the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even despite the fratrical war of recent years, Iraq society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterized by the contraindication - you can't rely on anyone and no agreements are kept.
Under these conditions, it is hard to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are used to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally correctly founded, remain only fake buildings, behind which the patriarchal tribal relations will continue to proliferate.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the confusion of the circumstances that complicate the influences of Pakistan and Iran even further.
Building an "active state" that is the minimalist goal of the whole operation is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama strategy alienated by his voluntarism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and now it is on the verge of explosion.
Believe in this, believe that the little soldiers who have broken out into the war cry about the "early homecoming" create a miracle here, can only be a truly romantic soul, which is not impressed by facts.
From a political point of view, the date for the withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, because the Taliban will take that up as the indirect confession of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in the battles in Afghanistan is running out.
Europe’s politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is related to the war in the Hindu Kush mountain range.
Another possible factor that can radically influence the situation is the development of events in Iran.
Should the situation continue to deteriorate and the increased sanctions do not affect the Iranians, a very serious question arises for the United States as to whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question must be answered in the period in which America is progressing to Obama for the winning withdrawal from Afghanistan.
However, any solution will also mean a dramatic turn of the Afghan situation.
The only consolation for Barack Obama is the fact that there are still three years left until the presidential election, and thus there is still enough time for him to be able to resort to a different strategy if it would prove to be a total failure.
